result.name: Trusty Gourmet

reviews.text: Pleasant, interesting almond favoured soup. You can get good pork lung soup here, which is very rare dish (hard to prepare). They are also famous pig liver.
Good cantonese food in old style
Good food with no MSG. I like it.
Good Food especially in Soup

I have never eaten at a place that does liver better than this. The liver is in huge slices that are not too thin and are cooked just nice, unlike other places that usually overcook it. The broth is rich and hearty with no MSG added which makes it a very healthy place to go to! The soup tastes different with and without noodles so try both! 
Came by twice and on my first time we also had the stir fried spicy organs which was absolutely delicious. It matched the salted vegetable very well.
I must also say the service is great and they are friendly (can be rare in HK), and the manager can speak a bit of English. We tried his homemade milk pudding and I like it a lot. Not too heavy on the milk and yet the consistency of the pudding is there. Will definitely be back!
